userPrompt: Build a Japanese language learning center from beginner to advanced. Cover all topics needed for fluency. Use romaji, hiragana and katakana only. Have in depth examples. Have a learning path with all information in a guided path. Have vocabulary, grammar and verb reference pages.
researchPlan:
TOPIC: Japanese Language Learning Center
SCOPE: N5 (Beginner) through N1 (Advanced)
WRITING: Romaji + Hiragana + Katakana only
SECTIONS: Overview, Learning Path (7 units, 20+ lessons), Writing Systems (hiragana/katakana charts), Grammar Reference (43 points), Vocabulary (8 categories, 100+ words), Verb Reference (16 verbs, 11 forms each), Particles (20 particles), Sources
KEY FEATURE: All content self-contained — no external links needed for learning

contentAnalysis.readabilityNote: Comprehensive Japanese language curriculum with guided learning path, interactive reference pages, and 200+ example sentences across all JLPT levels
